\f0\fs32 \cf0 intltool is a set of tools to centralize translation of many different file formats using GNU gettext-compatible PO files.\
The intltool collection can be used to do these things:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\ql\qnatural
\ls1\ilvl0\cf0 {\listtext	\'95	}Extract translatable strings from various source files (.xml.in, glade, .desktop.in, .server.in, .oaf.in).\
{\listtext	\'95	}Collect the extracted strings together with messages from traditional source files (.c, .h) in po/$(PACKAGE).pot.\
{\listtext	\'95	}Merge back the translations from .po files into .xml, .desktop and oaf files. This merge step will happen at build resp. installation time.}
